title: For Sale:  9mm black talon
postcontent: I have four boxes of Winchester Black Talon 9mm Luger 147 Gr. SXT Deep Penetrator ammunition 20 cartridges to a box.This stuff is rare in a white box with in a red block that states LAW ENFORCEMENT AMMUNITION #RA9SXN, this was suppose to be a hotter load. Originally designed and released in 1991 this cartridge was the first to include a pre-scored jacket. It also included a reverse taper design which allowed it's signature talons to be released perpendicular to the bullet upon impact. The black color of the bullet comes from the oxidized copper jacket and the LubaLox coating which was new for Winchester at the time. LubaLox protects the rifling of the barrel as well as provides lubrication for the bullet while traveling the length of the barrel. It is still used on many of their cartridges today minus the black color. In all Black Talon was cutting edge technology for it's time, thee best hollow point on the market. After a few mass shootings Black Talon proved it's effectiveness but in an unfortunately negative light. Without even being on the market for two years Winchester decided it was in the company's best interest to pull the Black Talon line in 1993. this is $60. each box of history. I can ship this . buyer must know the laws in their state.
